PERSONAL POLICY GUIDE via NewsNet
January 1, 1996

RIAS DISCOUNTS

The Retirement Insurance Advisory Service (RIAS) is giving discounts of
up to 15% to customers taking out a joint contents and buildings policy
as part of the RIAS Home Insurance Plan.  David Holden, RIAS general
secretary, said that its research showed that customers who choose to
cover their home contents and structure together under one policy are a
better risk than those who take out separate contents or buildings
cover.  RIAS home insurance policyholders can also add a special Home
Help Benefit to their existing cover for only #1 per month.  This
provides up to #50 per week for eight weeks should the policyholder
accidentally break or fracture a bone.



