January 8, 1996

CA-BASED W/C CARRIERS RANKED BY DIRECT LOSS RATIO, 1994 3RD QUARTER

SAN FRANCISCO - The third quarter 1995 workers' comp insurance figures for
California-based carriers, a regular feature in the Executive, are reported on
page 3.

The carriers are ranked according to their direct loss ratios with the highest
at the top of the page, lowest at the bottom. Keep in mind, the figures
represent each company's, or group of companies, total business writings, not
just those for California.

Fremont Indemnity of California, at the request of its management has been
separated from the other members of its group in order to reflect a more
accurate picture. Readers' attention is drawn to a boxed section, Direct
Premium Change, which reflects the percentage change between the current YTD
and previous YTD premiums.

A facsimile copy is available by calling the Workers' Comp Executive at
(916)477-8500.




