January 12, 1996

AIG

American International Group Inc (AIG), New York, and 20th Century
Industries, Los Angeles, have formed a joint venture to market and
service private passenger motor cover in Arizona, which will operate
under the name of 20th Century Insurance Co of Arizona and be 51% owned
by AIG.  Regulatory approval is expected in time for operations to
commence in the Spring.  The venture is the first undertaking completed
in the investment and strategic alliance agreement between AIG and 20th
Century, which was approved by 20th Century's shareholders in December.
 Under this agreement, AIG will invest US$216m in 20th Century.



