WORLD INSURANCE REPORT via NewsNet
January 12, 1996

1996 CAPACITY

Lloyd's underwriting capacity in 1996 will be #9.852m (US$15.3m), down
from #10.195m in 1995,  according to provisional figures.  Individual
names will contribute #6.841m (down from #7.835m), #2.586m through
bespoke underwriting and #4.255m through MAPAs, and corporate vehicles
#3.011m (up from #2.360m).  The number of individual names will fall
from 14,884 to 12,811 (only six new members joined for the year), and
the number of corporate names rise to 165 in 71 corporate member
groups.  25 new corporate names raised an additional #362m in capacity
for 1996, and existing corporate members increased allocated capacity
by #289m.



