chemical plant, Somerset West, 40km from Cape Town, operator African
Explosives and Chemical Industries (AECI), storing 15,000 tonnes of
sulphur.  Fire led to poisonous gas leak.  000's evacuated.  3 dead.

21.12.95, explosion, property damage

Taiwan:  pharmaceutical plant, Hsin-ying City, Tai-nan County,
explosion app 0920 local.  Est damage: more than NT$10m (US$366,046).
More than 20 injured.

22.12.95, fire, property damage, fatalities

Philippines:  Lian Tay commercial complex, Iligan City, 490 miles SW
Manila, fire destroyed app 40 commercial establishments.  8 dead.

23.12.95, explosion, property damage, fatalities

Colombia:  coal mine, La Biutrera, 7 miles S Cali, explosion.  7 dead,
5 missing.

24.12.95, fire, property damage

Germany:  factory, operator Kloeckner-Humboldt-Deutz AG (KHD), fire
destroyed app 15,000sqm manufacturing facilities.  Est damage:  DM100m
(US$69.4m).  Lead insurer: Gerling-Konzern Allgemeine Versicherungs AG,
Cologne.  Other insurers: Allianz Versicherungs AG, Colonia
Versicherungs AG, Nordstern Allgemeine Versicherungs AG and Haftpflicht
der Deutschen Industrie VVaG.  Loss reinsured by: Munich Re, Swiss Re
and in-house reinsurer Gerling-Konzern Globale Re.

24.12.95, fire, property damage, fatalities

India:  Rajiv marriage hall, Dabwali, Haryana state, app 140km N New
Delhi, fire started in tent during school prizegiving day ceremony,
igniting overhead canopy which collapsed on audience.  425 dead, 120
injured.  Suspected cause: electrical short circuit.  Chief minister
announced compensation of Rs100,000 (US$2,860) to families of dead,
Rs50,000 to families of injured.

25.12.95, fire, property damage

Germany:  public swimming pool, Frankfurt suburb, fire destroyed pool.
Est damage: DM20m (US$13.85m).

26.12.95, fire, property damage

US:  zoo, Philadelphia PA, fire spread through primate house, killing
23 rare gorillas, orangutans, gibbons and lemurs, app 0045 local.

26.12.95, fire, property damage

US:  swine research centre, 2,000 acre farm, 20 miles N University of
Wisconsin, Madison WI, fire destroyed 700 pigs used for medical
research and research data.  Est loss of building: US$5.3m.

26.12.95, pipeline rupture, oil spill

CIS:  Russia:  Urals-Siberian pipeline, linking Tyimazy, Omsk and
Novosibirsk, rupture nr Ufa caused oil spill.  Est 460 tonnes of crude
spilled.

31.12.95, fire, property damage

Pakistan:  godown, East Wharf, Karachi Port, fire started app 0200 GMT,
destroying 4,300 tonnes general cargo, non-toxic chemicals, news print
rolls and caustic soda worth "millions of rupees".  Port activity and
shipping movements at adjoining berths temporarily suspended.  (1.1)
Goods worth more than Rs60m (US$240m) destroyed.

31.12.95, fire, property damage

South Korea:  market building, Kwangmyung city, SW Seoul, fire started
app 0830 local, engulfing two-storey building.  App 150 shops destroyed
or damaged.

31.12.95, fire, property damage

Switzerland:  electroplating factory, Duebendorf, Zurich canton, fire
destroyed factory causing est damage of SF1m (US$862,738).  Suspected
cause:  overheated bath.

2.1.96, fire, property damage

China:  factory dormitory, Shenzhen Special Economic Zone, fire spread
through dormitory attached to factory manufacturing Christmas
decorations.  20 dead, 50 injured.  Suspected cause: fire started after
worker fell asleep while reading by candlelight.

3.1.96, fire, property damage

Australia:  George Patterson House, financial district, Sydney, fire
started in six-storey building, destroying roof and causing sections of
wall to collapse.

6.1.96, fire, property damage

Philippines:  commercial mall, San Juan district, Manila, fire engulfed
Virra Mall causing damage est at US$2.5m.  Suspected cause:  faulty
wiring.

6-7.1.96, fire, property damage

Germany:  textile company, Quakenbruck, nr Osnabruck, fire destroyed
two storage and production halls for textiles, sporting articles and
fabrics.  Est loss: DM13m (US$9m).



