January 1, 1996

Lion to begin feasibility study on Vietnamese market+

TOKYO, Dec. 25 Kyodo

     Dentifrice and synthetic detergent maker Lion Corp. will launch
a feasibility study in the Vietnamese market early next year, a
company official said Monday.
     The decision was made to catch up with rival maker Kao Corp.,
which recently announced establishment of a company in Vietnam to
prepare for production of such products as shampoos starting in 1997,
the official said.
     Lion has already signed a deal with a major Japanese trading
house to jointly launch the study on the household products market in
the country and search for a Vietnamese business partner, the
official said.
     Lion will make a decision whether to enter the Vietnamese market
within one or two years, he said.
     Lion entered the Thai market in 1958, its first foothold on the
Asian mainland, and currently makes detergents and other products in
six Asian countries, including China, the official said.



