CHINESE HIGHWAY OPENED

A 155km highway in China's north-west has been officially opened to
traffic according to the China Daily. Known as the Xian-Baoji highway,
it is the main section of a state road that will link China's coast to
the western provinces of Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai and Xinjiang. Xian is
Shaanxi's capital, while Baoji is its industrial hub. Construction on
the highway began in 1992, with Yn1.4bn ($168m) in investment of which
$30m was lent by the Kuwaiti government. Shaanxi authorities will
construct another 300km by the year 2000 which they intend to finance
by auctioning the management rights to the highway linking Xian to the
Terracotta Warrior tourist site.



