ADB APPROVES FINANCE FOR PORT PROJECT

The Asian Development Bank has approved a $63m loan and a technical
assistance grant of $490,000 to finance the second Yantai port project
in north-eastern China. The project involves the construction of two
container and two conventional cargo berths and related facilities at
Yantai port in Shandong province. The loan, which is to be sourced from
the Bank's ordinary capital resources, will be repaid over 24 years
including a grace period of four years. The interest rate is based on
the pool-based variable lending rate which currently stands at 6.9 per
